"n.奢侈逸乐的人 【英】 n.奢侈逸乐的人（lov er of luxury） 【考】 反义词：spartan(刚 毅的人); ascetic(禁欲者) n. 奢侈逸乐的人 【记】源于: Sybaris(锡巴里斯)古希腊城市, 曾因其富饶与奢靡而著名. Sy = see, bar, rite(n 仪式): 整天在酒吧里面看仪式－奢侈糜烂的人 【反】spartan(n 节俭的人); ascetic(n 禁欲者) 【记】see bar 常去看酒吧，看酒吧歌舞表演 sybarite (n.)  ""person devoted to pleasure,"" 1590s, literally ""inhabitant of Sybaris,"" ancient Greek town in southern Italy, whose people were noted for their love of luxury. From Latin Sybarita, from Greek Sybarites."
